<pre style="margin: 0em;">
Hi Jozsef,

On 2008/11/15, at 17:11, Jozsef Kovacs wrote:
</pre><blockquote style="border-left: #5555EE solid 0.2em; margin: 0em; padding-left: 0.85em"><tt>I simply replaced the sizeof part to a predefined size. It's ugly,  
</tt><tt>but I didn't want to modify the headers as they are part of *libc  
</tt><tt>and not mip6d. None of the structs in netinet/* are packed. I think  
</tt><tt>the correct fix would be to stop checking data taken from the  
</tt><tt>network against struct sizes assuming they will have the correct size.
</tt></blockquote><pre style="margin: 0em;">

</pre><tt>We unfortunately can't assume they would have the correct size as  
</tt><tt>forged packet could be used by malicious people against mip6d.
</tt><pre style="margin: 0em;">

Regards,
</pre><tt>romain 
</tt><tt>
